by Guikingone at 2026-05-13T07:56:50Z

Hi @vkost 👋🏻

Sorry for the delay, for the test, you can find inspiration in `OllamaApiCatalogTest` (wrong name BTW, something to change 😄):

```php
# ..
public function testModelCatalogCanReturnModelFromApi()
{
    $httpClient = new MockHttpClient([
        new JsonMockResponse([
            'capabilities' => ['completion'],
        ]),
    ], 'http://127.0.0.1:11434');

    $modelCatalog = new ModelCatalog($httpClient);

    $model = $modelCatalog->getModel('foo');

    $this->assertSame('foo', $model->getName());
    $this->assertSame([
        Capability::INPUT_MESSAGES,
        Capability::OUTPUT_STRUCTURED,
    ], $model->getCapabilities());
    $this->assertSame(1, $httpClient->getRequestsCount());
}
# ...
```

By adding a new test that change `completion` to `insert`, you can test that the `getCapabilities` array returns the new capability, should be enough for a first test 👍🏻

